From: Nickel Browser Team <team@nickel-browser.org>
Date: Thu, 01 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 07/10] nickel: fingerprint-protection — canvas/audio/font noise

Add a fingerprint-protection layer that injects calibrated noise into the
JavaScript APIs most commonly used for browser fingerprinting:

  - Canvas 2D / WebGL — adds per-session pixel-level noise to readback
  - AudioContext — offsets sample values by a tiny random delta
  - Navigator.hardwareConcurrency / deviceMemory — returns a rounded value
  - Screen.width / height / colorDepth — rounds to standard values
  - Date.prototype.getTimezoneOffset — returns UTC offset only

Each noise value is seeded from a per-profile secret so the same site
always sees the same (altered) fingerprint within a session, preventing
"inconsistency detection" countermeasures.

The implementation hooks Blink's bindings layer via a new
NickelFingerprintShield class that is instantiated per RenderFrame.
